\begin_layout Paragraph
investor sentiment
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
投资者对证券需求的变化(shifts in demand for securities)可能是完全理性的：reactions to public
 announcements that affect future growth rate of dividends, risk, or risk
 aversion；adjustment to news conveyed through the trading process itself；tax
 trading or trading done for institutional reasons of the types discussed
 above.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
但不是所有变化都是理性的，也可能是投资者对伪信息(pseudo-signals)的反应；或者是投资者使用了一些非弹性交易策略or所谓的“popular
 model”(从而出现了羊群效应？？？)。不过值得注意的是These demand shifts will only matter if they
 are correlated across noise traders，否则可能出现相互抵消从而整体行为表现出“理性”。many trading
 strategies based on pseudo-signals, noise, and popular models are correlated,
 leading to aggregate demand shifts.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Many of these persistent mistakes are relevant for financial markets.
 例如 overconfident (Alpert and Raiffa, 1982)导致 take on more risk；extrapolate
 past time series导致 chase trends (Andreassen and Kraus, 1988)；put too little
 weight on base rates and too much weight on new information (Tversky and
 Kahneman, 1982)导致 overreact to news.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
尽管如此，the argument that noise traders lose money and eventually disappear
 is not self-evident；Learning and imitation may not adversely affect noise
